definition.value: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-Bay-K-8644
An ortho- and peri-fused polycyclic arene that consists of a benzene ring fused with a acephenanthrylene ring.
An ortho- and peri-fused polycyclic arene consisting of five fused benzene rings. It is listed as a Group 3 carcinogen by the IARC.
A bisphenol that is methane in which two of the hydrogens have been replaced by 4-hydroxyphenyl groups.
A bisphenol that is bisphenol A condensed with two molecules of methacrylic acid.

An  3-oxo-Delta(1),Delta(4)-steroid substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a beta-hydroxy group at position 17. It is an  anabolic androgenic steroid that has been developed for veterinary use.
A monocarboxylic acid amide having a 2-phenylpropan-2-yl substituent attached to the amide nitrogen and a 1-bromo-2,2-dimethylpropyl group attached to the carbonyl carbon.
A halomethane that is dichloromethane in which oneof the hydrogens has been replaced by a bromine atom. It occurs as a contaminant in drinking water.
